📌 AI Trading Insights – Deep Dive
1. Core Concepts

At a Goldman Sachs level, AI in trading isn’t just about “predicting stock prices.” The focus is on data-driven decision-making, automation, and risk management:

Data Sources
Market data: prices, volume, order books
Alternative data: news, social media, satellite imagery
Macroeconomic indicators: GDP, interest rates, employment data
AI Use Cases
Price Prediction / Forecasting: Using time-series models, LSTMs, Transformers
Sentiment Analysis: NLP on news & social media to gauge market sentiment
Algorithmic Trading: Automated trading strategies based on signals from AI models
Risk Management: Portfolio optimization, Value-at-Risk (VaR), anomaly detection
Trade Execution: Smart order routing, minimizing slippage
Practical Implementation Notes
Feature Engineering is critical: rolling averages, technical indicators (RSI, MACD), volatility, momentum
Backtesting & Simulation: Evaluate strategies before deploying real capital
Latency-sensitive systems: Trading decisions must be milliseconds-fast; AI models must be optimized
Model Governance: Regulatory audits, explainability, and versioning are crucial
